## Operator Breakdown

- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: human|divine — Distinguishes between mortal striving and sacred encounter at the boundary where Jacob faces God.
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: wrestling|blessing — Wrestling and blessing are inseparable relational acts; the struggle is the medium of communion.
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: brokenness|new_identity — The dislocated hip becomes the gateway to the name Israel; wounding precedes and enables transformation.
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: persistence|spiritual_growth — Refusing to let go despite injury is the paradigmatic act of faith under duress, driving spiritual maturation.
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: struggle|surrender — Victory comes through dependence rather than dominance, cycling between striving and yielding.
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: injury|covenant — Physical wounding establishes covenantal identity; blessing comes at the cost of permanent mark.

